1
00:00:20,699 --> 00:00:25,111
There is no God!

2
00:00:37,382 --> 00:00:39,459
Forgive me.

3
00:00:44,347 --> 00:00:46,885
Give me a sign.

4
00:00:47,308 --> 00:00:49,015
Help me.

5
00:00:53,354 --> 00:00:57,019
Maureen. Maureen, where are you, dear?

6
00:00:57,442 --> 00:00:59,766
Maureen, where are you?

7
00:01:00,193 --> 00:01:02,437
Oh dear God. She's up there.

8
00:01:02,865 --> 00:01:04,655
Maureen!

9
00:01:05,074 --> 00:01:07,068
Stay where you are!

10
00:01:07,494 --> 00:01:09,202
Oon't move!

11
00:01:10,996 --> 00:01:14,781
Stay where you are.
- Come down!

12
00:01:16,878 --> 00:01:19,249
There is no God!

13
00:01:19,671 --> 00:01:22,424
Wretched girl, how dare you!
- Get away from me!

14
00:01:22,842 --> 00:01:24,750
Please, Maureen. You mustn't.

15
00:01:25,177 --> 00:01:29,175
You have an obligation to Him.
- I have nothing.

16
00:01:29,599 --> 00:01:34,225
I am nothing.
- You can't. - No!

17
00:01:45,570 --> 00:01:48,987
Wasn't your own sin red enough?
You'll burn in hell for this!

18
00:01:49,408 --> 00:01:51,816
You'll burn in hell!

19
00:01:54,123 --> 00:01:55,581
Maureen!

20
00:03:52,568 --> 00:03:56,482
Want a ride? Or do you have
the Olympic torch in the suitcase?

21
00:04:00,700 --> 00:04:03,155
Wouldn't want to lose ya.

22
00:04:03,786 --> 00:04:06,536
Oon't worry.
I ain't born again or nothing.

23
00:04:06,955 --> 00:04:10,290
I'll get this junk out of your way.

24
00:04:10,710 --> 00:04:13,202
Jesus just come with it
when I bought her used.

25
00:04:13,631 --> 00:04:17,544
I wanted to replace it
with a magnetic compass,

26
00:04:17,968 --> 00:04:20,672
but you usually end up
going the wrong direction anyway.

27
00:04:21,095 --> 00:04:23,847
That makes two of us.
- Yeah?

28
00:04:28,226 --> 00:04:30,931
Water?
- Thank you.

29
00:04:32,437 --> 00:04:35,643
Name's Ouane Ouke, by the way.
Friends just call me Ouke.

30
00:04:39,071 --> 00:04:43,779
Put the suitcase in the back seat.
- Thank you.

31
00:04:45,285 --> 00:04:47,361
Hey, watch the guitar!
- I'm sorry.

32
00:04:47,788 --> 00:04:52,247
No harm done.
Just watch out. It's my life.

33
00:04:52,666 --> 00:04:57,293
Going to LA to be a rock-n-roll star.
What about you? Where you going?

34
00:04:57,713 --> 00:05:00,881
What were you doing back there?
- I...

35
00:05:01,302 --> 00:05:05,344
Car trouble?
- Yes. I had car trouble.

36
00:05:05,763 --> 00:05:07,257
What kind?

37
00:05:09,642 --> 00:05:15,760
Ah, no car.
- No car? That's the worst kind.

38
00:05:16,188 --> 00:05:19,521
Still don't know where you come from.
- So?

39
00:05:19,942 --> 00:05:23,987
Are you my Father confessor?
- Jesus,

40
00:05:24,405 --> 00:05:28,867
I was just asking! You act as if
I accused you of murder or something.

41
00:05:29,494 --> 00:05:33,824
Hey, it's none of my business.
Play mystery lady if you want.

42
00:05:34,249 --> 00:05:38,911
I don't care where you come from.
Could've fallen from the sky.

43
00:05:39,336 --> 00:05:42,336
A little angel
just tumbled off her cloud.

44
00:05:42,755 --> 00:05:47,132
Well, hold on angel,
I'll get you where you're going.

45
00:06:02,276 --> 00:06:04,149
Get out of here!

46
00:06:14,661 --> 00:06:16,653
Come on, baby.

47
00:06:25,213 --> 00:06:27,455
You alright?
- Yes.

48
00:06:48,444 --> 00:06:51,480
What are you doing? - It's as
far as we go in this shit, honey.

49
00:06:51,905 --> 00:06:55,904
But it could rain all night.
- That's right.

50
00:06:59,204 --> 00:07:01,196
Better get some sleep.

51
00:07:54,424 --> 00:07:57,673
Excuse me. I'm sorry.

52
00:08:00,220 --> 00:08:02,628
You kind of slid over.

53
00:08:03,056 --> 00:08:05,262
It's still raining.

54
00:08:07,938 --> 00:08:11,221
Why did you do that?
- Why didn't you stop me?

55
00:08:11,648 --> 00:08:15,183
I didn't have time.
- I'll give you another chance.

56
00:08:16,319 --> 00:08:21,028
I'm not very good at this.
- You could have fooled me.

57
00:08:22,784 --> 00:08:24,408
Please don't!

58
00:08:29,581 --> 00:08:32,747
Oh, well, I guess
we got him a little excited.

59
00:08:34,213 --> 00:08:35,410
Oon't!

60
00:08:36,339 --> 00:08:37,418
No!

61
00:08:39,717 --> 00:08:42,552
What's the problem, angel?

62
00:08:43,553 --> 00:08:45,593
Get away from me!

63
00:08:51,226 --> 00:08:55,807
Are you crazy? Get in here!
- Give me my suitcase.

64
00:09:01,114 --> 00:09:02,311
Stupid bitch!

65
00:09:02,739 --> 00:09:05,989
You could've been coming
instead of going.

66
00:11:49,355 --> 00:11:52,854
Are you really my mother?
- The name Spool means nothing to you?

67
00:11:53,277 --> 00:11:56,859
No. Should it?
- It was Norma Bates' maiden name.

68
00:11:57,280 --> 00:11:59,735
The woman you thought was
your mother was my sister.

69
00:12:00,157 --> 00:12:03,573
She never mentioned me, did she?
- No.

70
00:12:03,994 --> 00:12:06,449
You sure you won't have a sandwich?

71
00:12:07,625 --> 00:12:09,415
Pardon?

72
00:13:26,950 --> 00:13:28,194
Hi there.

73
00:13:31,244 --> 00:13:33,119
Be right down.

74
00:14:01,024 --> 00:14:02,186
Room?

75
00:14:04,610 --> 00:14:07,444
I'd love one,
but I don't think I can afford it.

76
00:14:07,862 --> 00:14:10,898
You should keep the register closed.
Somebody'll steal you blind.

77
00:14:11,323 --> 00:14:14,194
Wouldn't get them very far.
- Business slow?

78
00:14:14,619 --> 00:14:19,446
You're my first customer of the day.
Or did you just need directions?

79
00:14:19,876 --> 00:14:23,954
I was actually interested in the sign.
But if business is bad...

80
00:14:24,379 --> 00:14:28,044
No, it's not bad, just slow.

81
00:14:31,261 --> 00:14:35,173
Well, 12 cabins, 12 vacancies...
We've been closed for a while.

82
00:14:35,597 --> 00:14:38,551
Renovations.
But life's picking up along here.

83
00:14:38,975 --> 00:14:40,884
Good prices, good service.
Things'll pick up.

84
00:14:41,311 --> 00:14:44,893
I've got a rebuilt ice machine,
and 4 cabins booked for this week.

85
00:14:45,647 --> 00:14:49,184
Fairvale High's Homecoming.
Big game against Central.

86
00:14:50,195 --> 00:14:53,565
I'm rattling on.
Yes, there is a job. Interested?

87
00:14:53,991 --> 00:14:58,238
In money? The only honest way
to get it is to earn it or inherit it.

88
00:14:58,662 --> 00:15:02,195
And I don't have any rich relatives.
Got an application form?

89
00:15:02,624 --> 00:15:05,161
Not necessary. My name is Norman,

90
00:15:05,584 --> 00:15:07,541
Norman Bates.

91
00:15:09,046 --> 00:15:11,998
What'ya been painting?
- Oh, I'm sorry.

92
00:15:12,423 --> 00:15:17,169
Step into the back while I clean up.
- Said the spider to the fly.

93
00:15:23,644 --> 00:15:27,723
Local branch of the Audubon society?
- My hobby. Stuffing things.

94
00:15:28,147 --> 00:15:32,441
Have a seat...
- Ouane Ouke. Just call me Ouke.

95
00:15:33,069 --> 00:15:35,109
I can pay you 5 dollars an hour.

96
00:15:35,530 --> 00:15:39,277
You'd work the desk,
make beds, clean up. Stuff like that.

97
00:15:41,912 --> 00:15:45,446
Want some of these?
You'd be general assistant.

98
00:15:45,874 --> 00:15:49,491
Work's not too hard,
and you'd have lots of free time.

99
00:15:50,253 --> 00:15:54,248
I'm the manager,
so you'd be assistant manager.

100
00:15:54,672 --> 00:15:59,464
You'd get a free room and work days.
I prefer the nights.

101
00:15:59,885 --> 00:16:01,927
I've got to be honest, Norm.
- Norman.

102
00:16:02,347 --> 00:16:05,928
I just want to make enough bucks
to get my car fixed and

103
00:16:06,353 --> 00:16:09,721
build up a little stake for LA.
I'm a singer.

104
00:16:11,439 --> 00:16:15,484
But I could fill in until you found
somebody permanent. I'm just not

105
00:16:15,902 --> 00:16:17,445
staying too long.

106
00:16:19,530 --> 00:16:22,317
No one ever does.

107
00:16:23,658 --> 00:16:26,529
Your cabin's at the end.
Why don't you go unpack?

108
00:16:26,953 --> 00:16:29,907
I need to get back to the house.

109
00:16:31,290 --> 00:16:34,127
You live up there?
- Yeah.

110
00:16:34,920 --> 00:16:36,829
Me and myself, alone.

111
00:16:43,554 --> 00:16:47,550
You clear on the credit card machine?
- Yeah, I used to be a pump jockey.

112
00:16:47,973 --> 00:16:52,101
The rooms cost...
- 20.95 single, 25.95 double.

113
00:16:52,519 --> 00:16:55,853
I'll bring you a couple of burgers.
- Alright!

114
00:17:00,820 --> 00:17:05,114
Still beats the hell out of me.
Just doesn't show up for work one day.

115
00:17:05,574 --> 00:17:09,405
Thought you would've turned up
some clues by now, John.

116
00:17:09,828 --> 00:17:15,035
Her apartment's all in order.
Oidn't say anything to her landlord.

117
00:17:15,458 --> 00:17:19,538
You'd think she'd tell me
if she was going to take a month off.

118
00:17:19,962 --> 00:17:21,920
Emma Spool
was as regular as clockwork.

119
00:17:22,340 --> 00:17:25,790
I don't think she missed a day
in the? years I've owned this dump.

120
00:17:26,220 --> 00:17:31,213
I hope that nothing's happened to her.
- You mean like Norman Bates?

121
00:17:32,183 --> 00:17:37,178
Oidn't they work here together?
They say he likes older women.

122
00:17:37,897 --> 00:17:41,560
Rumors and innuendo caused
that boy enough trouble.

123
00:17:41,982 --> 00:17:45,434
What's your interest anyway?
- I drove from LA to see him.

124
00:17:45,861 --> 00:17:48,982
Why? You another relative
of somebody he killed?

125
00:17:49,407 --> 00:17:51,862
It's really not any of your business.

126
00:17:52,284 --> 00:17:54,113
Keeping the peace is my business.

127
00:17:54,538 --> 00:17:57,823
Then until I've broken some law,
lay off the third-degree, OK?

128
00:17:58,250 --> 00:18:00,823
Can't you just leave
the poor slob alone?

129
00:18:01,253 --> 00:18:06,495
What are you? His fan club?
- No, we believe in second chances.

130
00:18:06,924 --> 00:18:10,044
What Norman did was a long time ago,
and he paid the price.

131
00:18:10,468 --> 00:18:12,461
It depends on who you ask.

132
00:18:12,887 --> 00:18:15,888
20 years in the bunk house
is paying the price, girly.

133
00:18:16,307 --> 00:18:17,932
The guy's okay now.

134
00:18:18,350 --> 00:18:21,555
When he worked here,
he was always on time and reliable.

135
00:18:21,980 --> 00:18:24,187
A real Employee of the Month!

136
00:18:24,943 --> 00:18:30,233
Go ahead and talk smart, lady.
He just wants to be left in peace.

137
00:18:30,656 --> 00:18:37,107
Now look, Norman Bates has suffered
enough. Just leave him...

138
00:18:38,537 --> 00:18:40,660
Afternoon, sheriff.
- ... alone.

139
00:18:41,082 --> 00:18:43,750
Mrs. Oudley...
- What'll it be, Norman?

140
00:18:44,875 --> 00:18:47,368
Chicken fried steak is good today.

141
00:18:47,797 --> 00:18:52,008
Alright, and a glass of milk, please.
And a couple of burgers to go.

142
00:18:52,426 --> 00:18:54,798
I'm warning you. I don't want trouble.

143
00:18:55,221 --> 00:18:59,467
Then let go of my arm
or I'll holler police brutality.

144
00:19:01,267 --> 00:19:05,810
Mind if I join you, Mr. Bates?
Tracy Vanderbilt.

145
00:19:08,275 --> 00:19:10,101
Thanks, Myrna.

146
00:19:11,526 --> 00:19:13,901
Coastal Reports?
- I write for them sometimes.

147
00:19:14,322 --> 00:19:17,690
If you don't mind, I'd like to ask you
a few questions. - I mind.

148
00:19:18,118 --> 00:19:21,736
Mr. Bates... - Norman.
- I'm writing on the insanity defense

149
00:19:22,162 --> 00:19:24,914
and the rehabilitation
of mentally ill murderers.

150
00:19:25,332 --> 00:19:29,412
Many people think
they can't be rehabilitated

151
00:19:29,836 --> 00:19:32,124
and there shouldn't be
an insanity defense.

152
00:19:32,546 --> 00:19:37,754
We hear the objections of the victims
and relatives, but the murderers,

153
00:19:38,177 --> 00:19:43,764
who can't help themselves,
are victims too. What do you think?

154
00:19:44,183 --> 00:19:47,020
If this lady's bothering you,
I'll have her leave.

155
00:19:47,688 --> 00:19:50,143
Isn't your coffee break over, sheriff?

156
00:19:54,317 --> 00:19:56,358
Anything else, Norman?

157
00:19:57,862 --> 00:20:01,446
What do you think?
- About? - What we were just saying.

158
00:20:01,867 --> 00:20:06,197
You were incarcerated for 20 years.
- 22.

159
00:20:06,664 --> 00:20:10,531
Right.
For 22 years, you were locked away.

160
00:20:10,959 --> 00:20:13,498
The state says you're sane.
You paid your debt.

161
00:20:13,921 --> 00:20:17,171
Then Lila Loomis starts
to persecute you. - Because of

162
00:20:17,592 --> 00:20:19,548
what happened to her sister.
- Yes.

163
00:20:19,968 --> 00:20:22,174
Marion Crane. Right?

164
00:20:30,310 --> 00:20:33,479
Right.
- But that was 20 years ago.

165
00:20:33,898 --> 00:20:35,273
22.

166
00:20:35,691 --> 00:20:38,478
A long time to harbor revenge.

167
00:20:38,903 --> 00:20:43,149
Aren't you bitter about
what Lila Loomis tried to do to you?

168
00:20:44,450 --> 00:20:45,694
I understand.

169
00:20:46,118 --> 00:20:48,691
My cure
couldn't cure the hurt I caused.

170
00:20:49,121 --> 00:20:52,405
My return to sanity
didn't return the dead.

171
00:20:52,832 --> 00:20:54,872
There's no way
to make up that loss.

172
00:20:55,293 --> 00:20:58,079
The past is never really past.

173
00:20:58,503 --> 00:21:02,206
It stays with me all the time.
No matter how hard I try,

174
00:21:02,634 --> 00:21:07,177
I can't escape. It's always there.
Throbbing inside you.

175
00:21:07,597 --> 00:21:11,925
Coloring your perceptions of the world,
and sometimes controlling them.

176
00:21:12,351 --> 00:21:14,259
That's my point, Norman. You have

177
00:21:14,685 --> 00:21:17,556
a conscience. You live with guilt.
You punish yourself all the time.

178
00:21:18,731 --> 00:21:20,855
Why does the rest of society have to?

179
00:21:21,276 --> 00:21:25,023
Take Mrs. Spool's disappearance.
What if a well-meaning citizen

180
00:21:25,446 --> 00:21:27,986
thought that
you had something to do with it?

181
00:21:35,498 --> 00:21:38,369
I'm not upsetting you, Norman?
All this talk

182
00:21:38,793 --> 00:21:41,164
is only hypothetical.
- What's yours, babe?

183
00:21:41,586 --> 00:21:45,037
She is only an example
of how people might,

184
00:21:45,465 --> 00:21:47,375
given your past history,

185
00:21:47,968 --> 00:21:52,512
tend to automatically blame you
for any murder in the area.

186
00:22:13,450 --> 00:22:16,570
You're not going, Norman?
I'd like to talk to you again.

187
00:22:18,496 --> 00:22:21,368
You're not going to stiff us, Norman?

188
00:22:23,002 --> 00:22:27,794
Excuse me. Could you tell me,
is there a cheap place to stay here?

189
00:23:49,209 --> 00:23:50,491
Hello, angel.

190
00:23:51,878 --> 00:23:53,456
You work here?

191
00:23:53,879 --> 00:23:56,714
It's called suffering for one's art.
I'm sorry about last night.

192
00:23:57,132 --> 00:23:59,884
I was a little road-weary.
I'm glad you didn't drown.

193
00:24:00,303 --> 00:24:01,677
I'm so very tired.

194
00:24:02,096 --> 00:24:05,012
You won't find another place close.

195
00:24:06,060 --> 00:24:11,397
Oon't worry. Aside from total boredom,
nothing will happen to you here.

196
00:24:24,576 --> 00:24:27,910
Maureen Coil. Pretty name.

197
00:24:28,538 --> 00:24:32,454
How much?
- For a single, $25.95.

198
00:24:45,346 --> 00:24:47,835
There you go, angel.
Enjoy your stay.

199
00:25:13,331 --> 00:25:17,279
Your type, Norm?
- You gave her Cabin 1.

200
00:25:18,001 --> 00:25:20,493
Makes it kind of cosy.

201
00:25:21,088 --> 00:25:24,787
Clean her up a little,
she'll look pretty good.

202
00:25:39,898 --> 00:25:44,025
Put me closer to the window.
- Someone will see you, Mother.

203
00:25:44,443 --> 00:25:46,732
Are you ashamed of me?

204
00:25:47,155 --> 00:25:50,653
You know why, Mother. They've
even written about you in the paper.

205
00:25:51,073 --> 00:25:55,025
Stop your whining, boy.
All this fuss over nothing.

206
00:25:55,872 --> 00:25:58,327
Not nothing. I saw her.

207
00:25:58,750 --> 00:26:03,458
Even the initials on the suitcase.
M.C., Marion Crane.

208
00:26:03,879 --> 00:26:08,921
Another of your cheap,
erotic delusions.

209
00:26:09,343 --> 00:26:13,126
You killed her.
The slut deserved it. But she's dead.

210
00:26:13,555 --> 00:26:15,677
And the dead don't come back.

211
00:26:17,141 --> 00:26:19,895
You came back.
- I never went away.

212
00:26:20,312 --> 00:26:25,021
Oon't you know that by now?
You can't get rid of me.

213
00:26:25,734 --> 00:26:28,059
I'll always be with you, Norman.

214
00:26:28,777 --> 00:26:30,321
Always.

215
00:26:31,030 --> 00:26:33,780
Stand up straight and
wipe your snotty little nose.

216
00:26:34,198 --> 00:26:39,655
If the disgusting little whore upsets
you so much, just get rid of her.

217
00:26:40,079 --> 00:26:41,077
No!

218
00:26:45,334 --> 00:26:48,088
Then maybe I will.

219
00:27:10,108 --> 00:27:14,272
You have an obligation, Maureen.
Maureen, don't!

220
00:27:14,697 --> 00:27:16,855
There is no God.

221
00:27:17,283 --> 00:27:22,573
Please Maureen, you mustn't.
Get away. You'll burn in hell.

222
00:27:22,997 --> 00:27:26,993
You have an obligation.
I have nothing.

223
00:27:27,416 --> 00:27:30,334
I am nothing.

224
00:27:56,653 --> 00:27:59,404
What'll it be?
- Give me a beer.

225
00:28:12,919 --> 00:28:13,915
Hi.

226
00:28:15,629 --> 00:28:18,334
I'm Ouane.
- No kidding?

227
00:28:22,302 --> 00:28:25,635
Any objections
to a guy buying you a drink?

228
00:28:26,055 --> 00:28:29,674
I got a drink.
- So have another.

229
00:28:30,102 --> 00:28:32,891
You got a limit?
- Only to my patience.

230
00:28:33,314 --> 00:28:37,014
You don't have to call me Ouane.
- No, I don't. - Friends call me Ouke.

231
00:28:37,443 --> 00:28:39,400
I had a dog named Ouke once.
- Really?

232
00:28:39,820 --> 00:28:44,446
Scratch my belly, my leg'll shake.
- I hated the mutt.

233
00:28:49,245 --> 00:28:52,827
Keep the matches, lady. You need 'em.
You're as warm as a cry for help.

234
00:28:54,833 --> 00:28:57,667
Just a minute. Ouke. Ah, Ouane.

235
00:28:59,089 --> 00:29:02,124
Whatever. I'm easy.
- I've noticed.

236
