01:01:17,310 --> 01:01:18,343
Hello?

481
01:01:19,438 --> 01:01:21,927
You have a john?

482
01:01:50,177 --> 01:01:51,291
Men!

483
01:02:02,229 --> 01:02:05,015
Hey, where'd you come from?

484
01:02:05,982 --> 01:02:09,931
Geez, you scared the piss out of me.

485
01:02:11,696 --> 01:02:13,653
Oo you mind, sister?

486
01:02:14,073 --> 01:02:17,029
This is occupado.

487
01:02:42,599 --> 01:02:43,847
Ouke?

488
01:03:12,255 --> 01:03:16,003
Hey, innkeeper, I need change!
- Charlie, I got it.

489
01:03:46,495 --> 01:03:49,246
Get away from me.

490
01:03:50,248 --> 01:03:53,119
Looks like someone's getting lucky!

491
01:04:34,082 --> 01:04:35,910
What's happening?

492
01:04:36,336 --> 01:04:38,127
Come on, Leo.

493
01:04:40,131 --> 01:04:43,333
Oon't go up there.
- Why? Something's wrong with Norman?

494
01:04:43,758 --> 01:04:46,877
It's time somebody told you.

495
01:05:09,617 --> 01:05:14,112
Good morning, Norman. It's a bit hot
to be sleeping so late, isn't it?

496
01:05:14,537 --> 01:05:16,660
We had a lot of revelers last night.
- I know.

497
01:05:17,081 --> 01:05:20,782
One didn't come home.
Name is Patsy Boyle.

498
01:05:21,210 --> 01:05:24,995
She came with a group of locals
to party after the game.

499
01:05:25,966 --> 01:05:30,259
When they all left around 3,
nobody noticed that she wasn't there.

500
01:05:30,679 --> 01:05:35,090
Someone's missing and you come to me.
- There have been other accusations.

501
01:05:35,515 --> 01:05:37,803
From that reporter! She knows nothing.

502
01:05:38,225 --> 01:05:42,057
That's what we're going to find out.
Now it's too hot to argue.

503
01:05:42,480 --> 01:05:46,312
That rain made everything more muggy.
- Nothing back there. - Of course not.

504
01:05:46,735 --> 01:05:49,022
Please get out of my house.
- Sorry, Norman.

505
01:05:49,448 --> 01:05:54,522
We have the warrant.
It's in everybody's best interest.

506
01:05:55,577 --> 01:05:57,985
Who's? There's nothing here.
I didn't do anything.

507
01:05:58,414 --> 01:06:02,742
Then there's nothing to worry about.
Norman, come back!

508
01:06:04,334 --> 01:06:07,003
Get him, Leo. Ooggone you!

509
01:06:30,859 --> 01:06:34,727
Norman,
what the hell's the matter with you?

510
01:06:40,702 --> 01:06:42,160
Mother?

511
01:06:47,083 --> 01:06:48,662
I'm sorry, Norman.

512
01:06:49,754 --> 01:06:53,336
All seems a little unnecessary now.
- That's okay.

513
01:06:53,758 --> 01:06:57,801
Still no reason to get so...
so riled up.

514
01:06:58,219 --> 01:07:00,544
We'll leave you alone now. Again,

515
01:07:00,972 --> 01:07:04,176
I'm sorry. - That's not enough.
You just can't let it lie!

516
01:07:04,601 --> 01:07:08,182
I've had enough
of this Nancy Orew horseshit.

517
01:07:09,232 --> 01:07:11,638
I'm letting it lie and so are you.

518
01:07:12,359 --> 01:07:17,601
Until I have evidence to the contrary,
both ladies are missing persons.

519
01:07:18,031 --> 01:07:19,988
Aren't you going to question him?

520
01:07:20,408 --> 01:07:23,822
Why not drag the swamp?
He dumped the last bodies there.

521
01:07:24,243 --> 01:07:26,734
Oon't tell me my job,
Ms. Vanderbilt.

522
01:07:27,163 --> 01:07:29,369
Somebody has to.

523
01:07:29,790 --> 01:07:34,204
You're not going to let him go?
- Oespite all your glib insinuations,

524
01:07:34,628 --> 01:07:37,916
I don't have one iota of proof.
- He didn't do it.

525
01:07:38,342 --> 01:07:41,046
Norman was with me
until 6 o'clock this morning.

526
01:07:41,470 --> 01:07:43,712
Whatever happened to that girl,

527
01:07:44,139 --> 01:07:47,306
he didn't have anything to do with it.
- Well, Miss,

528
01:07:49,602 --> 01:07:53,301
had you told us sooner, you would
have saved us a lot of trouble.

529
01:07:53,730 --> 01:07:56,731
No one asked me.
- Come on, Leo.

530
01:07:57,526 --> 01:07:59,981
Bad time to beat the street, Norman.

531
01:08:00,403 --> 01:08:03,359
You'd better follow
the sheriff's example.

532
01:08:03,782 --> 01:08:09,370
I'm taking a passenger. Ready?

533
01:08:20,673 --> 01:08:23,543
She told you about me, didn't she?
- Yes.

534
01:08:23,968 --> 01:08:25,841
Where are you going?

535
01:08:27,471 --> 01:08:31,256
Father Brian said I could come stay
with him if I needed to.

536
01:08:31,684 --> 01:08:33,841
Please let me go.

537
01:09:06,091 --> 01:09:07,337
Mother!

538
01:09:10,928 --> 01:09:12,127
Mother!

539
01:09:39,248 --> 01:09:41,536
Mother, where are you?

540
01:10:46,520 --> 01:10:50,139
I love the silver
that shines in your hair.

541
01:10:50,567 --> 01:10:54,694
And the brow that's all furled
and wrinkled with care.

542
01:10:55,112 --> 01:10:59,062
I kissed the dear fingers,
so toilworn for me.

543
01:10:59,491 --> 01:11:04,450
Oh God bless you and keep you,
dear Mother...

544
01:11:05,497 --> 01:11:06,612
Bates.

545
01:11:09,336 --> 01:11:12,371
It doesn't scan, does it, Norman?

546
01:11:13,254 --> 01:11:14,335
But...

547
01:11:14,757 --> 01:11:17,544
a lot of shit around here doesn't.

548
01:11:17,968 --> 01:11:19,795
What are you doing with my mother?

549
01:11:20,596 --> 01:11:22,089
Oon't you mean...

550
01:11:22,513 --> 01:11:24,090
Mummy?

551
01:11:27,601 --> 01:11:30,175
You did a nice job on her, Norman.

552
01:11:30,604 --> 01:11:32,892
Fresh as the day she was croaked.

553
01:11:36,278 --> 01:11:37,225
Why?

554
01:11:37,653 --> 01:11:39,396
Just looking out for you.

555
01:11:39,821 --> 01:11:43,026
And yourself.
- I have ambitions, dreams.

556
01:11:43,451 --> 01:11:46,119
But dreams don't come cheap nowadays.

557
01:11:46,537 --> 01:11:48,992
I could have turned
Mom over to the cops,

558
01:11:49,414 --> 01:11:52,864
but all I would have gotten
was a pat on the back.

559
01:11:54,043 --> 01:11:56,664
That reporter
would've shelled out a few bucks,

560
01:11:57,088 --> 01:12:01,878
and gotten the lion's share
of the credit, a five-figure salary,

561
01:12:02,303 --> 01:12:04,590
and a big news job.

562
01:12:05,013 --> 01:12:09,342
Fine for her dreams,
but what about mine? No.

563
01:12:09,767 --> 01:12:14,761
I figure Mama's greatest value to me
is in her value to you.

564
01:12:15,188 --> 01:12:17,596
I don't have that kind of money.
- Oon't gripe to me.

565
01:12:18,024 --> 01:12:20,942
With that big piece of real estate
and this thriving business,

566
01:12:21,361 --> 01:12:25,109
you could just sell an acre.

567
01:12:25,740 --> 01:12:28,408
Please, Ouke.
I want my mother back.

568
01:12:28,828 --> 01:12:32,196
Take her. You know what I want.

569
01:12:33,080 --> 01:12:36,166
And you know what I'll do
if I don't get it.

570
01:12:36,585 --> 01:12:38,541
I know.

571
01:12:44,048 --> 01:12:47,168
I'm going to kill you,
you little freak.

572
01:13:03,486 --> 01:13:05,607
You think I'm stupid, Ouke?

573
01:13:07,072 --> 01:13:11,282
Even if I gave you money,
you'd still tell on Mother.

574
01:13:11,701 --> 01:13:14,369
No one must know what she did.

575
01:13:18,081 --> 01:13:19,824
She can't help it.

576
01:13:20,250 --> 01:13:24,877
She can't help the things she does.
She's just an old lady.

577
01:13:25,297 --> 01:13:26,957
A sick, old lady.

578
01:13:36,558 --> 01:13:38,183
Watch the guitar!

579
01:13:48,526 --> 01:13:52,738
You shouldn't sneak up
on a guy like that, Ouke. Ouke?

580
01:13:53,992 --> 01:13:57,407
I didn't mean it.

581
01:13:59,997 --> 01:14:03,946
You made me do this!
Your tainted blood in me!

582
01:14:06,294 --> 01:14:10,708
Oon't laugh at me, Mother.
Oon't laugh at me.

583
01:14:13,634 --> 01:14:18,593
I didn't even know she had any kids.
- Wasn't it on her job application?

584
01:14:19,016 --> 01:14:21,685
She was already here
when I bought the place? years ago.

585
01:14:22,102 --> 01:14:26,515
Best waitress I ever had.
- She worked for the previous owner?

586
01:14:26,940 --> 01:14:30,556
Harvey Leech. - Where's he now?
- He used to be in a nursing home.

587
01:14:30,984 --> 01:14:34,317
Outside town.
- Probably dead now.

588
01:14:40,868 --> 01:14:43,622
Spool?
- Emma Spool.

589
01:14:44,040 --> 01:14:47,574
She worked in your diner.
- Oiner?

590
01:14:48,377 --> 01:14:52,790
Yeah, I had a diner once.
- Mrs. Spool used to work for you.

591
01:14:53,215 --> 01:14:57,875
I had a woman named Spool
who used to work for me. A waitress.

592
01:14:58,302 --> 01:15:00,294
She come from that place.
- Place?

593
01:15:00,720 --> 01:15:04,422
That place for nuts. As-s-asylum.

594
01:15:04,849 --> 01:15:07,138
Mrs Spool was in an asylum?

595
01:15:07,559 --> 01:15:10,811
Asylum, that's it, asylum.

596
01:15:11,232 --> 01:15:13,805
You know, she killed somebody.

597
01:15:14,653 --> 01:15:17,653
Who?
- Somebody. Husband?

598
01:15:20,824 --> 01:15:25,900
I don't recall. Good waitress, Spool.

599
01:15:28,914 --> 01:15:32,698
Are you sure, Maureen?
- Oh yes.

600
01:15:33,127 --> 01:15:36,295
Norman understands me.
He understands forgiveness.

601
01:15:36,714 --> 01:15:40,462
I failed so many people, Father.
I won't fail him.

602
01:15:40,885 --> 01:15:45,345
That's why Mary came to me
the night he saved my life.

603
01:15:45,764 --> 01:15:48,006
It was a sign.

604
01:15:49,976 --> 01:15:54,934
And the woman in the window.
That must've been Mary too.

605
01:16:30,850 --> 01:16:32,723
I'll be back, Mother.

606
01:18:45,603 --> 01:18:50,016
Miserere mei, Oeus...

607
01:20:06,304 --> 01:20:10,883
I thought if she saw these copies
she might change her story.

608
01:20:12,895 --> 01:20:14,803
Can I see her?

609
01:20:15,230 --> 01:20:16,937
I'm afraid not.

610
01:20:41,296 --> 01:20:42,411
Norman!

611
01:21:12,826 --> 01:21:15,743
Norman? It's me.

612
01:21:17,580 --> 01:21:19,822
I've come back.

613
01:21:26,965 --> 01:21:29,883
I never should've gone away.

614
01:21:31,802 --> 01:21:35,421
Whatever happened to you in your past,

615
01:21:35,848 --> 01:21:39,132
I know you're good. You took a life,

616
01:21:39,559 --> 01:21:42,097
but you also saved a life.

617
01:21:42,520 --> 01:21:44,064
My life.

618
01:21:44,940 --> 01:21:47,097
Let it be your life.

619
01:21:49,196 --> 01:21:50,358
Oh, Norman!

620
01:21:53,908 --> 01:21:57,442
What happened to you?
- I slipped in the mud.

621
01:21:58,203 --> 01:21:59,781
I slipped too.

622
01:22:00,205 --> 01:22:03,039
I know I've hurt you.

623
01:22:03,457 --> 01:22:05,782
Can you forgive me?
- Norman!

624
01:22:23,395 --> 01:22:25,637
Maureen? Maureen?

625
01:22:35,404 --> 01:22:38,109
Mother!

626
01:22:49,586 --> 01:22:50,960
Maureen?

627
01:23:32,543 --> 01:23:35,118
Get that whore out of my house!

628
01:23:35,548 --> 01:23:39,294
Throw her down in the mud,
filth, where she belongs.

629
01:23:40,802 --> 01:23:44,252
I'll get you for this, Mother.
I'll get you for this.

630
01:23:45,055 --> 01:23:48,424
You haven't got the guts, boy.

631
01:25:47,128 --> 01:25:50,499
You dumb, stupid,

632
01:25:50,925 --> 01:25:53,595
naive girl.

633
01:26:01,852 --> 01:26:05,185
Why can't you leave my poor son,
my Norman, alone?

634
01:26:15,533 --> 01:26:20,075
What set you off again, Norman?
You killed Mrs. Spool, didn't you?

635
01:26:22,205 --> 01:26:25,123
Oid she tell you
that she was your mother?

636
01:26:25,542 --> 01:26:28,578
She was crazy, Norman,
but she wasn't your mother.

637
01:26:29,003 --> 01:26:30,830
Neither are you!

638
01:26:32,923 --> 01:26:35,759
She was your aunt,
and in love with your father.

639
01:26:36,177 --> 01:26:39,959
But your mother stole him
away from her. Emma Spool...

640
01:26:40,387 --> 01:26:46,094
killed your father in a jealous rage
and kidnapped you as a baby.

641
01:26:50,648 --> 01:26:54,812
She killed your father
because she thought you were hers.

642
01:26:55,861 --> 01:26:58,778
The child
she should've had with him.

643
01:27:01,699 --> 01:27:03,159
She was crazy.

644
01:27:03,578 --> 01:27:08,371
They locked her away.
- It's lies, it's all lies.

645
01:27:09,626 --> 01:27:12,495
She's a lying whore.
- Norman, where are you?

646
01:27:12,920 --> 01:27:14,794
She's a slut.

647
01:27:18,175 --> 01:27:21,425
Oon't let her talk about me like that.

648
01:27:23,847 --> 01:27:25,470
Norman, please listen to me!

649
01:27:26,098 --> 01:27:32,183
Norman, Mrs. Bates! Whoever you are.
It doesn't matter to me.

650
01:27:32,604 --> 01:27:35,607
Get her, boy.
Get her, just like the others!

651
01:27:38,903 --> 01:27:42,355
Get her!
- No! No!

652
01:27:42,783 --> 01:27:47,278
Oon't! Oon't! Please! Norman!

653
01:27:47,703 --> 01:27:48,734
No!

654
01:27:50,163 --> 01:27:54,457
Norman, can't you do anything right?

655
01:27:56,211 --> 01:28:01,088
How dare you treat your mother
in such ways.

656
01:28:03,719 --> 01:28:06,589
So, I don't have the guts, huh?

657
01:28:48,259 --> 01:28:51,464
I was for you, Norman.
Believed in you.

658
01:28:52,306 --> 01:28:55,428
You made a fool of me.
Look what you did to yourself!

659
01:28:55,852 --> 01:28:57,512
Why, Norman, why?

660
01:28:57,937 --> 01:29:01,852
Good God, son,
you'll never get out again.

661
01:29:04,318 --> 01:29:05,979
They're going to lock you up forever.

662
01:29:07,529 --> 01:29:11,857
But I'll be free.
I'll finally be free.

